BENIN – The National Directorate of Employment (NDE) has commenced the training of 50 unemployed youths on Agricultural Extension in Edo. Mallam Abubakar Fikpo, Director General, NDE, while speaking at the flagging off ceremony of the training in Benin on Tuesday said the training cuts across the three senatorial districts of Edo state. Fikpo, represented by the state Coordinator, Mr Solomon Edobor, said the Rural Employment Promotion of the Directorate would supervise the Agricultural Extension referred to as Agricultural Advisory Services. Pension Review: Kebbi Pensioners Give Government Ultimatum NSE, Getjob, Organises Job Fair For 1000 Applicants He said Agricultural Advisory Services would play a crucial role in boosting productivity, increase food security, improve rural livelihood and promote agriculture which is an engine of economic growth. He also said that the Agricultural Advisory Services is one of the activities in the Agricultural value-chain with the potential for youth employment in the rural sector hence, reducing rural/Urban drift. “Agricultural Extension Personnel in rural communities are crucial in boosting agricultural productivity hence the need to train unemployed youths . ” Also the average age of our farmers is between 40 and above thus, there is the need to train them on scientific and technology driven services thereby guarantee disease free production, yield high quality and stress free processing of farm products.” he said. According to him, the Agricultural Services is one of the Federal Government initiatives in curbing unemployment in the country . POLL He enumerated the objectives of the scheme as to generate employment for trained agricultural extension personnel , to remove the drudgery associated with the traditional farming practice, increase food production as well as to stimulate the rural economy and improve farming techniques among others.